\section{Introduction}
Channel capacity is the maximum rate at which one can transmit over a channel which can guarantee an arbitrarily small probability of error in transmission. However, channel capacity can be achieved as closely as required with codes of very large codeword lengths. But large codewords require more time units to transmit. Therefore it is useful to know the variation of the maximum rate at which one can transmit as a function of channel parameters and codeword length (see \cite{PPV1}).

